│ block may temporarily have multiple or not-yet-connected predecessors, causing getSinglePredecessor to return null and triggering the assert. A robust fix is to gracefully handle this  │
│ by falling back to the current CFG predecessor tracked in VPTransformState (State.CFG.PrevBB), which represents the predicating block used earlier (e.g., when creating the conditional  │
│ branch). I'll modify the code to use PredicatedBB->getSinglePredecessor() when available; otherwise, use State.CFG.PrevBB instead of asserting.                                          │
